  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nI start beacon-chain with this argouments (and others):\r\n\r\n```\r\n--enable-db-backup-webhook true --db-backup-output-dir=/home/ethereum/backup/\r\n```\r\nIf i run \r\n```\r\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:8080/db/backup\r\n```\r\nNothing happen, no response for severals minutes (hours), and than the curl process just kills themself or somthing like that.\r\nIn beacon-chain logs I can see immediatly\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2021-01-24 18:46:58\" level=info msg=\"Writing backup database.\" backup=\"/home/ethereum/.eth2/beaconchaindata/backups/prysm_beacondb_at_slot_0484434.backup\" prefix=db\r\n```\r\nBut that file is just 110mb.\r\nSo I believe that the backup is not done.\r\n\r\nIf I do the same steps with the validator I can see a response on the curl side \"OK\". And the backup file is about 736kB\r\nAlso as you can see my \"--db-backup-output-dir\" is ignored, I don't know why.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nNope. Tried 1.0.4 and 1.1.0 version\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\nI'm running prysm on raspberry with this ubuntu image https://github.com/diglos/pi-gen\r\nOn pyrmont network.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
